{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9aed9d35-b69a-4cf1-85c0-92f3239b2bb2","content":"You're on **MSTest 3.8.2** / .NET 9. In MSTest v3, `TestContext` is injected via the **constructor** (the old settable-property pattern still works but is legacy). Here's the recommended approach:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n\n    // TestContext injected via constructor\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n        // Synchronous init goes here (or in [TestInitialize])\n    }\n\n    // Sync per-test init\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public void Setup()\n    {\n        // runs before each test\n    }\n\n    // Async per-test init\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        // async work before each test\n        await Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void ExampleTest()\n    {\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Hello from test\");\n        Assert.IsTrue(true);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **Constructor injection** — pass `TestContext` as a constructor parameter; MSTest v3 resolves it automatically.\n- **`[TestInitialize]`** — can return `void` (sync) or `Task` (async). You can have both on separate methods.\n- **`[ClassInitialize]`** — for one-time class-level setup; also supports `async Task`. It receives `TestContext` as a parameter: `static async Task ClassInit(TestContext ctx)`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e59680b3-a96a-41c7-8d84-dff4ad9f091c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"They're using MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9.0. In MSTest v3, `TestContext` is injected via the constructor rather than the old property-based approach. Let me provide guidance on the modern patterns.\n\nKey points for MSTest 3.x:\n1. `TestContext` is injected via constructor\n2. `[TestInitialize]` for sync init, can also be async (returns `Task`)\n3. `[ClassInitialize]` for class-level init\n4. Constructor injection of `TestContext` replaces the old property pattern\n\nLet me give a concise, accurate answer.","outputTokens":541,"requestId":"0C06:2DCDB0:3DCF68:4867C5:69F00E19"},"id":"a54c27db-c0c0-4011-8e85-0ae139509b9e","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:32:21.059Z","parentId":"8751f13b-5a77-4db3-bc2a-d86f1b678269"}
